					Full Description



Valley National Bancorp, incorporated in 1983, is the bank holding company for Valley National Bank (the Bank). The Bank provides a range of commercial, retail, insurance and wealth management financial services products. The Company's segments include Consumer Lending, Commercial Lending, Investment Management, and Corporate and Other Adjustments. The Consumer Lending segment primarily includes residential mortgages, home equity loans and automobile loans. The Commercial Lending segment primarily includes floating rate and adjustable rate commercial and industrial loans, as well as fixed rate owner occupied and commercial real estate loans. The Investment Management segment includes the Company's investments in various types of securities. As of July 26, 2017, the Bank had 200 branch locations serving northern and central New Jersey, the New York City boroughs of Manhattan, Brooklyn, Queens and Long Island, and Florida.The Bank provides a range of banking services, including automated teller machines, telephone and Internet banking, remote deposit capture, overdraft facilities, drive-in and night deposit services, and safe deposit facilities. The Bank also provides certain international banking services to customers, including standby letters of credit, documentary letters of credit and related products, and certain ancillary services, such as foreign exchange, documentary collections, foreign wire transfers and the maintenance of foreign bank accounts are available products and services, as well as transaction accounts for non-resident aliens. The Bank's subsidiaries include an insurance agency offering property and casualty, life and health insurance; an asset management advisor that is a registered investment advisor with Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC); title insurance agencies in New Jersey, New York and Florida; subsidiaries that hold, maintain and manage investment assets for the Bank; a subsidiary that owns and services auto loans; a subsidiary that specializes in healthcare equipment lending and other commercial equipment leases, and a subsidiary that owns and services New York commercial loans.Commercial Lending SegmentThe Commercial Lending segment includes commercial and industrial loans, and commercial real estate loans. The Company makes commercial loans to small and middle market businesses generally located in the New Jersey and New York area, as well as Florida. Its commercial loan products include term loans for equipment purchases, working capital lines of credit that assist its customers' financing of accounts receivable and inventory, and commercial mortgages for owner occupied properties. The Company, through its leasing subsidiary, Highland Capital Corp., provides financing to the medical equipment leasing market. The Company also offers taxi medallion loans. The Company originates commercial real estate loans that are primarily secured by multi-unit residential property, and non-owner occupied commercial, industrial and retail property within New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania and Florida. As of December 31, 2016, the Company's commercial and industrial loans totaled approximately $2.6 billion. As of December 31, 2016, its commercial real estate loans and construction loans totaled $9.5 billion.Consumer Lending SegmentThe Company offers a range of residential mortgage loans for the purpose of purchasing or refinancing one- to four-family residential properties. The Bank is also a servicer of residential mortgage portfolios. Its other consumer loan portfolio includes direct and indirect automobile loans, home equity loans and lines of credit, loans secured by the cash surrender value of life insurance, and secured and unsecured other consumer loans, including credit card loans. The Company is an auto lender in New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Connecticut, Delaware and Florida, offering indirect auto loans secured by either new or used automobiles. Its Wealth Management Division provides coordinated and integrated delivery of asset management advisory, trust, general insurance, title insurance and trust services. Its trust services include living and testamentary trusts, investment management, custodial and escrow services, and estate administration, primarily to individuals. Its asset management advisory services include investment services for individuals and small to medium sized businesses, trusts and custom tailored investment strategies designed for various types of retirement plans. As of December 31, 2016, the Company's residential mortgage loans totaled approximately $2.9 billion. As of December 31, 2016, its other consumer loans totaled $2.2 billion.Investment Management SegmentThe Company's investment management segment includes investments in various types of securities. As of December 31, 2016, the Company's total investment securities and interest bearing deposits with banks were $3.2 billion and $171.7 million, respectively.

