CAREERS
More Info & Help


Visualize a New Beginning.

                  Are you ready for a change? Looking for career advancement? Take the next step. Begin by exploring our career site to review the opportunities we have available.
               
Who is Valley National Bank?

                  Valley National Bank is a recognized leader throughout the financial services industry for its outstanding performance, diversified products and a history of customer service. With a wide variety of consumer and business products, over $23 billion in assets, and with over 200 branches, we're one of the largest commercial banks headquartered in New Jersey. The key to our success comes down to one simple thing: the dedication and commitment of Valley employees. Learn more about our history.
               
Why apply to Valley?

                  Valley is a financial institution with a proven track record of performance that continues to seek growth throughout New York and New Jersey. Our focused strategy for expansion creates career opportunities for enthusiastic and motivated individuals who are willing to grow with us. We look for candidates who have the desire and drive and possess the knowledge, skills and experience that will contribute to our success.
               

                  All employees must comply with all regulations pertaining to the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA), the USA Patriot Act and rules issued by the Office of Foreign Assets (OFAC).  It is also required that employees complete annual BSA training and that those in supervisory positions ensure this training in completed by their staff.  It is the responsibility of all employees to report to the AML/BSA Compliance Department any suspicious or criminal activity or any attempt to avoid BSA reporting requirements on the part of customers or employees.
               
Click here to view our current listings

                  Valley National Bank is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a diverse workforce. We consider all qualified applicants without regard to race, religion, color, sex, national origin, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or veteran status, among other factors. Applicants with a disability that need assistance applying for a position may call 973-305-8800, extension 4040 or email valleyjobs@valleynationalbank.com.
               
Valley National Bank is an Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer.












